  "texts": [
    "Large language models (LLMs) such as ChatGPT (GPT-4) have shown significant promise as tools in enhancing healthcare delivery.",
    "LLMs have previously demonstrated capabilities in various medical domains, such as passing medical licensure exams, diagnosing disease states, and clinical decision making.",
    "[1] [2] [3] [4] Within the field of clinical pharmacy, the performance of LLMs have been partially explored by testing for deprescribing benzodiazepines, identifying drug-herb interactions, and performance on a national pharmacist examination, showing promise.",
    "[5] [6] [7] [8] There have been calls for thoughtful evaluation and regulation of artificial intelligence prior to implementation in the healthcare setting.",
    "9 Limited studies have evaluated the potential of LLMs to evaluate medication regimens, identify drug-drug interactions (DDIs), and provide clinical recommendations to potentially serve as a supportive tool in clinical pharmacy."
  ],
